article.headline: Neal has career day, Ball State wins MAC opener 52-24
article.description: Riley Neal passed for 402 yards and four touchdowns -- two in the first quarter -- and ran for another score as Ball State walloped Kent State 52-24 in a Mid-American Conference opener for both teams on Saturday.
article.linkText: Neal has career day, Ball State wins MAC opener 52-24

images.name: Ball State's Neal completes 4th TD pass
images.caption: Ball State QB Riley Neal rips a pass to Riley Miller for a 33-yard touchdown pass.

video.headline: Ball State's Neal completes 4th TD pass
video.caption: Ball State QB Riley Neal rips a pass to Riley Miller for a 33-yard touchdown pass.
video.title: Ball State's Neal completes 4th TD pass
video.description: Ball State QB Riley Neal rips a pass to Riley Miller for a 33-yard touchdown pass.

article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. -- Riley Neal passed for 402 yards and four touchdowns -- two in the first quarter -- and ran for another score as Ball State walloped Kent State 52-24 in a Mid-American Conference opener for both teams on Saturday. His 402 yards was a career-best in a single game for Neal and the seventh 400-yard passing game in the program's history, first since 2013. After faking a handoff left, Neal bolted through the line over right guard and sprinted 31 yards untouched for the game's final score. Kent State had allowed only 10 first-half points in its first three games, but Ball State scored three touchdowns on its first four possessions, leading 21-0 with 3:47 left in the opening quarter, and posted 35 points by halftime. Woody Barrett completed 30 of 44 passes for 314 yards and a score. Isaiah McKoy caught 10 passes -- the first time since 2016 a Golden Flashes receiver had that many receptions in a game. -------------- More AP college football: https://apnews.com/tag/Collegefootball and https://twitter.com/AP-Top25
